Unify microscope + acquisition presets into one imaging preset

Drops the two-tier preset model (microscope preset referenced by
acquisition preset) in favor of a single "imaging preset" that bundles
hardware state and camera settings together: objective, filter, lamp,
IL shutter/ND, plus exposure_ms, binning, and pseudo-color. Apply
pushes everything to the scope and camera in one shot; loading from
the timeline applies it the same way.

Renames the `presets` config module to `imaging`, rebuilds the
Microscope Setup preset card with inline exposure/binning/color
inputs, and removes the now-redundant Acquisition Presets card from
Camera Setup.
